\vec{a}, \vec{b}
A_{base} = \frac{1}{2}|\vec{a} \times \vec{b}| = \frac{1}{2}|-3\hat{x} + \hat{y} + 2 \hat{z}| = \sqrt{14}/2.
\vec{a}, \vec{b}
-3x + y + 2z = 0
h = \frac{-3(3) + 1(2) + 2(5)}{\sqrt{14}} = \frac{3}{\sqrt{14}}.
V = \frac{1}{3}A_{base}h = \frac{1}{3} \frac{\sqrt{14}}{2} \frac{3}{\sqrt{14}} = \frac{1}{2}.
